uss the relevance of the so-called Jupiter-Saturn barrier phenomenon.\nFinally, we show how the Oort spike in the 1/a-distribution of near-parabolic\ncomets is built from both dynamically new and old comets. We also point out\nthat C/2007 W1 seems to be the first serious candidate for interstellar\nprovenience.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Mon, 5 Jan 2015 19:53:51 GMT"}],"update_date":"2015-06-23"}
